  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat the oven and prepare the potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Set the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6. Boil a kettle.</p>\r\n<p>Cut narrow slices (about the width of a pound coin) into the&nbsp;<strong>waxy&nbsp;potatoes</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base &ndash; these are your<strong>&nbsp;hasselback&nbsp;potatoes</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Tip: rest the potatoes on to a wooden spoon when cutting, it will prevent you from cutting all the way through the potato!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast your hasselback potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>hasselback&nbsp;potatoes</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray (use&nbsp;tin foil&nbsp;to avoid mess!), drizzle each with&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;and season with&nbsp;<strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 35-40 minutes or until they're tender and starting to crisp.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the peas and pea shoots </strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>garden peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 minutes or until they're tender.</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>peas</strong> are tender, add most of the&nbsp;<strong>pea shoots</strong>&nbsp;(save a small handful for garnish!) and cook for 30 seconds or until wilted.</p>\r\n<p>Once wilted, drain and set aside. Reserve the pan for step 5.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the shallots and stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Re-boil a kettle.</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>shallots</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the&nbsp;pea velout&eacute;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Return the pot to a medium heat with 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong>. Once melted, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until softened.</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes further or until starting to thicken.</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>drained peas</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>pea shoots</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>creamy stock</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong>&nbsp;and blend until smooth.</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1528.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the asparagus and toast the almonds </strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the potatoes are almost cooked, add the <strong>asparagus spears</strong> to the tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 5-8 minutes or until the <strong>asparagus</strong> is tender with a slight bite.</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a separate baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 minutes or until lightly toasted.&nbsp;</p>",
